  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>GE Café in LA — style-first premium for design-forward kitchens</h2>
    <p>Café's distinguishing move among premium stoves is the finish + hardware customization approach. Matte White + Matte Black + Platinum Glass finishes give Café an aesthetic that doesn't look like mass-market stainless — and the customizable-hardware handles mean owners can match handle finish to cabinet hardware (brass handles with brass cabinet pulls, chrome with chrome, black with matte black) without custom manufacturing. For design-forward LA households that want premium stove with specific aesthetic, Café is a distinct offering at $2,500-$8,000 that competes with Bosch 800 Series design-matte, Samsung premium style-focused tiers, or specialty color-brand stoves at higher pricing.</p>
    <p>Service approach on Café respects the finish. Matte White + Matte Black surfaces require masking during interior-component service; abrasive cleaners damage the matte coat so we use soft-cloth + mild cleaner protocols during work. Customizable-hardware swap is owner-DIY — we don't bill for handle service unless mounting hardware was damaged during owner-swap attempt. Our LA Café service concentrates in Silver Lake + Los Feliz + Echo Park + Highland Park Eastside design-district households, Venice + Santa Monica architectural remodels, Studio City + Atwater Village family-design kitchens, Pasadena + South Pasadena + Hermosa Beach aesthetic-driven upgrades.</p>
  </div></section>

